#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/navigate/navigation.rst:129
#, fuzzy
msgid "If you get lost in 3D space, which is not uncommon, two hotkeys will help you: :kbd:`Home` changes the view so that you can see all objects :menuselection:`View --> Frame All`, while :kbd:`NumpadPeriod` zooms the view to the currently selected objects when in perspective mode :menuselection:`View --> Frame Selected`."
msgstr "If you get lost in 3D space, which is not uncommon, two hotkeys will help you: :kbd:`Home` changes the view so that you can see all objects :menuselection:`Góc Nhìn (View) --> Hiển Thị Toàn Bộ (View All)`, while :kbd:`NumpadPeriod` zooms the view to the currently selected objects when in perspective mode :menuselection:`Góc Nhìn (View) --> Hiển Thị cái được Chọn (View Selected)`."

